# Commit Conventions

All commit messages MUST follow **Conventional Commits** and be written in **English**.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>
```

- **Max 100 characters** for the full first line (type + scope + description)
- **Lowercase** description, no period at the end
- Use imperative mood ("add", "fix", "update" — not "added", "fixes")

## Allowed Types

`feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`

## Examples

```
# ✅ GOOD
feat(auth): add google oauth login flow
fix(api): handle null response from payment gateway
chore(deps): bump next.js to 16.1.0
refactor(hero): extract animation hook from component

# ❌ BAD — Portuguese
feat(auth): adicionar login com google

# ❌ BAD — too long (over 100 chars)
feat(authentication): add comprehensive google oauth login flow with token refresh and session management

# ❌ BAD — missing type
update header component styles

# ❌ BAD — past tense
fix(api): fixed null pointer in user service
```

## Breaking Changes

Use `!` after type/scope and add a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer:

```
feat(api)!: remove deprecated /v1/users endpoint

BREAKING CHANGE: /v1/users has been removed, use /v2/users instead
```
